the bash for that is beautiful

```
if [ -z "$1" ]
  then
    echo "No argument supplied!"
    exit
fi

echo "Downloading <https://api.scryfall.com/sets/$1>"
curl "<https://api.scryfall.com/sets/$1>" > /home/ubuntu/edhrec/json/scryfall/${1}.json

i=0

while true; do
        i=$((i+1))
        echo working on page $i

        ofile=/home/ubuntu/edhrec/json/scryfall/${1}-cards${i}.json

        curl "<https://api.scryfall.com/cards/search?format=json&order=set&page=$i&q=%2B%2Be%3A$1>" > $ofile

        grep -q '"has_more":false' $ofile && break
done

echo "Download complete"
ls -lah /home/ubuntu/edhrec/json/scryfall/$1.json
ls -lah /home/ubuntu/edhrec/json/scryfall/$1-cards*.json
```
